  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Thrombocytopenia is defined as platelets of less than 150 x 10\n3\n/mcL.  Symptoms such as bruising and petechiae usually occur at counts at 50 x 10\n3\n/mcL and between 5-10x 10\n3\n/mcL there is a high risk of spontaneous bleeding.",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Nonpalpable\npetechiae\n/purpura\nMucosal bleeding (gingival,\nepistaxis\n)\nMenorrhagia\n,\nhemoptysis\n,\nhematuria\n,\nhematochezia\nDeep tissue/joint bleeding is less common (more likely due to\ncoagulopathies\n)",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
